_source.text: [6] measured the noise exposure and hearing thresholds of Chicago Symphony Orchestra musicians and found the sound levels to be at 75-95 dB(A), corresponding to an 8-h daily L eq , and although the musicians' mean hearing thresholds of 59 dB were better than those of an unscreened non-industrial population, 52.5% of the individual musicians showed notched audiograms consistent with NIHL.
